==English==
===Transitive verb===
'''to pistol-whip'''
{{wikipediapar|pistol-whipping}}
#To [[strike]] or [[beat]] someone with a [[pistol]]. Especially with the [[butt]].

===Examples===
Future tense: "He broke your [[pistol]]? What are you going to do? You can't shoot him with it." "No, but I can pistol-whip him until he runs out of [[stupid]]."

Present tense: "What are you doing?" "I'm pistol-whipping this poor [[sod]] for being an [[idiot]]."

Past tense: "Remember when I pistol-whipped you for breaking my [[firearm]]?"